{"nodes": [{"id": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design", "label": "Host-Owned Server Health Design Spec", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_serverhealth", "label": "serverHealth Host State Machine", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "With N windows there were N independent recovery loops with visibly drifting countdowns. The Bun host already proxies every GitLab request, so it is the natural choke point: passive detection classifies every request outcome (no webview 'report down' RPC), one recovery loop (backoff 2/5/15 + 1s countdown), and broadcast to all windows. The probe must not re-enter observe() \u2014 no feedback loop. Takes probe fn + broadcaster as collaborators so it unit-tests without electrobun."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_confirm_then_latch", "label": "Confirm-Then-Latch Auth Rule", "file_type": "rationale", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A single transient 401 must not log the user out: an auth outcome while ok triggers a cooldown-guarded confirm probe, and only a confirmed failure latches 'expired'. These semantics are well-tested in useSession today and must be ported to serverHealth.observe with equivalent tests, not dropped."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_broadcast", "label": "Window Registry + lumen:server-health Broadcast", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "A unified Set of all BrowserWindows; broadcast iterates and executeJavascripts a CustomEvent dispatch into each. Broadcasting to a not-yet-ready webview is harmless (no listener); the getServerHealth boot pull seeds late-joiners."}, {"id": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_installserverhealth", "label": "installServerHealth Webview Mirror", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Windows become thin displays: sessionState is written ONLY by the health listener (no local detection); installAuthWatch, probeServer, and the useServerRecovery probe loop are removed. On a down\u2192ok transition each window invalidates its own queries since each window owns its own cache."}], "edges": [{"source": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_serverhealth", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_confirm_then_latch", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design", "target": "specs_2026_06_10_host_server_health_design_broadcast", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "docs/superpowers/specs/2026-06-10-host-server-health-design.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "sp